model

Interface ModelAPI

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Observable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    Model

    public interface ModelAPI
extends Observable
    Interface representing main model component of the Vector Racer system, it is the game data and logic. Implementing classes should handle all functionality and data structures for running the game.

      • createEmptyRacetrack

        void createEmptyRacetrack(int rows,
                          int cols,
                          int startPosRow,
                          int startPosCol,
                          int finalZone)
        Creates a new racetrack in the model with the specified dimensions and spawn location for players' vehicles.
        Parameters:
        rows - the number of rows high that the RacetrackAPI should be
        cols - the number of columns wide that the RacetrackAPI should be
        startPosRow - the row on which players' vehicles should spawn
        startPosCol - the column on which players' vehicles should spawn
        finalZone - the last zone that vehicles should be in before they can finish the race by passing into a goal
